  int b;
  p1 = &b; //rightthe assigned value of p1 can be changed
   *p1 = 1; //wrongthe object value cannot be changed by p1
  ```

  + the assigned value of an const pointer cannot be changed

  ```c++
  int a;
  int * const p2 = &a;
  p2 = &b; //wrongp2 is a const pointer which cannot be changed
  ```

